{"url": "https://myhoustonmajic.com/3296324/chadwick-boseman-and-lupita-nyongo-explain-their-magnetic-chemistry-in-black-panther/", "text": "Chadwick Boseman and Lupita Nyong\u2019o star in Marvel\u2019s Black Panther (in theaters now.) Boseman plays King T\u2019Challa and Lupita plays his off-and-on girlfriend Nakia, and they have chemistry on screen. Nyong\u2019o credits director Ryan Coogler with that visible chemistry, saying Boseman himself is a \u201cmagnetic person.\u201d She adds, \u201cChemistry is something that you pray for as an actor, because it\u2019s so hard to fabricate. It\u2019s so much easier to just have it and work on other things\u2013 your intention, your action, and all that. To try and fabricate chemistry is another\u2026 it\u2019s a lot of energy.\u201d Boseman added that while they\u2019re not dating in real life, \u201cIt\u2019s not hard to fall in love with Lupita. She\u2019s a beautiful person. She\u2019s intelligent, strong, assertive. You fall in love with people when you see them in their light, when you see them doing what they do, and they illuminate a certain aura.\n\n\u2715", "images": ["https://myhoustonmajic.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/33/2025/10/17600247305156.png?strip=all&quality=80&w=150&crop=0,0,100,150px", "https://myhoustonmajic.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/33/2025/11/17621814176909.jpg?quality=80&strip=all&w=1024&crop=0,0,100,733px", "https://myhoustonmajic.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/33/2025/10/17600247305156.png?strip=all&quality=80&w=1600&crop=0,0,100,896px", "https://myhoustonmajic.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/33/2014/11/27653d7cfdf7f1cf967c5fa6e1ec3fdcfd857c18_large.jpeg?quality=80&strip=all&w=150&crop=0,0,100,150px", "https://myhoustonmajic.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/33/2025/11/17630309083296.png?strip=all&quality=80&w=700&crop=0,0,100,400px", "https://rickeysmileymorningshow.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/56/2025/11/17622075448106.jpg?quality=80&strip=all&w=350&crop=0,0,100,200px", "https://myhoustonmajic.com/w